OL,3,CFarage appears to row back on re-
OL,4,Copening Port Talbot's blast furnaces
OL,6,FNigel Farage has appeared to row back
OL,7,Fon a commitment to re-open the blast
OL,8,Ffurnaces at Port Talbot's Tata Steel
OL,9,Fplant.
OL,11,FOn a visit to Merthyr Tydfil on
OL,12,FThursday (16 April) Mr Farage seemed
OL,13,Fto dial back commitment to the policy
OL,14,Fwhen asked why it was not in the
OL,15,Fparty's Senedd Election manifesto. He
OL,16,Fsaid that to do so "would be very
OL,17,Fexpensive" and was a matter for the
OL,18,F"national government not devolved
OL,19,Fgovernment".
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/9
