OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F468A1776694271
OL,3,CFarage appears to row back on re-
OL,4,Copening Port Talbot's blast furnaces
OL,6,FTata Steel closed the last blast
OL,7,Ffurnace on the Port Talbot steelworks
OL,8,Fsite in September 2024, putting over
OL,9,F2,800 jobs at risk and marking the end
OL,10,Fof traditional steel-making in the
OL,11,Ftown.
OL,13,FWhilst accompanying Reform UK Wales
OL,14,F:eader Dan Thomas on a Senedd Election
OL,15,Fcampaign trail on Thursday, Mr Farage
OL,16,Fwas questioned on why the policy to
OL,17,Freopen the blast furnaces was not
OL,18,Fincluded in his party's manifesto.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,469,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F468A1776694271
OL,3,CFarage appears to row back on re-
OL,4,Copening Port Talbot's blast furnaces
OL,6,FHe said: "Once you've closed a primary
OL,7,Fblast furnace, to get it going again
OL,8,Ftakes forever.
OL,10,F"I've said it for years. I've said for
OL,11,Fyears you'd finish up with Wales no
OL,12,Flonger being a steel producer because
OL,13,Fof insane net zero policies and we've
OL,14,Fseen this.
OL,16,FMr Farage added: "It's very, very
OL,17,Fexpensive. And it should have been
OL,18,Fsomething done by national government
OL,19,Fnot devolved government."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
