PN,46807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F468A1776694271
OL,3,CFarage appears to row back on re-
OL,4,Copening Port Talbot's blast furnaces
OL,6,FThe Reform leader received a warm
OL,7,Freception in Merthyr Tydfil, with
OL,8,Flocals stopping him to ask for photos
OL,9,Fand business owners sharing their
OL,10,Ffrustrations.
OL,12,FClaire James, 39, stopped Mr Farage in
OL,13,Fthe street to take a photo for her son
OL,14,FBrooklyn, 16, who she said is
OL,15,F"obsessed" with the politician.
OL,17,FShe said: "My nan has always voted
OL,18,FLabour, and she'd be turning in her
OL,19,Fgrave now if she'd seen the way the
OL,20,Fcountry was today, it's disgusting,
OL,21,Fit's vile.
OL,26,@wD@AOUwD@JO]yD@KOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,469,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F468A1776694271
OL,3,CFarage appears to row back on re-
OL,4,Copening Port Talbot's blast furnaces
OL,6,F"I think (Reform) can turn it around,
OL,7,Fjust give them a chance.
OL,9,FPenny Fisher, 61, who previously voted
OL,10,FConservative, said: "We've got a small
OL,11,Fbusiness and it's hard with Labour, so
OL,12,F(Farage) is fab, he's got great
OL,13,Fpolicies, and that's why I'm voting
OL,14,FReform.
OL,16,F"I like him as a person, he comes
OL,17,Facross as (though) he's telling the
OL,18,Ftruth for once."
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@UOUxD@AOUzD@PO]
